channel.title: Which Type Of Web Browser Do You Prefer?
channel.description:
Well, Which web browser do you prefer? i've posted some web browsers that may not be known. But blame wikipedia for that thats where i have recieved all my info here i've put an "Other" option for some wikipedia may not have covered for some reason You can also have discussion why you believe you're web browser if preferred over another.
This should be some very intresting "Discussions" I also forgot to mention that you can vote for more than one web browser. But I guess it's pretty obvious
---------EDIT----------
Here are the links to the maxthon and seamonkey browsers so you can see more info on them.

item.title: Which Type Of Web Browser Do You Prefer?
item.dc:creator: @MistaBigBoss MistaBigBoss
item.description:
@MistaBigBoss wrote:

[quote=“xryz, post:42, topic:411777”][quote author=MistaBigBoss link=topic=513029.msg3724877#msg3724877 date=1314201942]
The thing is, the latest Internet Explorer is extremely FAST, I mean, open this site with Chrome and then with the LATEST version of IE, it’s just amazing, I had never expected to discover this.

This site = http://musiccanbefun.edankwan.com/

So atm, I just use what I feel like using, most of the time Chrome, but I also use Firefox and IE. These 3 browsers have their pros and cons wich is why I combine them all together to get the best web expierience.
[/quote]

wow that is surprising about the site, but there must be a reason why the performance is so much less on chrome than it is with ie. its almost like they use feature that only ie specializes on. i mean look at this site: http://html5test.com/ my cellphones browser(default android froyo browser) support more html5 than ie9 does.

ie doesnt have webgl nor does it have web workers. Im usually a google fanboy, and pretty much against anything microsoft. i only use ie when it is absolutely necessary, like to use the itacademy website. you can’t use the ie tab extension for chrome on that website.[/quote]Yeah well, HTML5 is still new and some browsers have more support in certain areas than others but I’m sure all browsers will adapt in time.
